quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
7,68,"I convey to you the messages of my Lord, and I give you sincere advice."
7,69,"Do you wonder that an exhortation should come to you from your Lord through a man from amongst yourselves that he may warn you? And do call to mind when He made you successors after the people of Noah and amply increased you in stature. Remember then the wondrous bounties {1} of Allah, that you may prosper.'",footnotes:1:The word ala' used in the above verse stands for bounties
7,70,"They said: 'Have you come to us that we should worship none other than Allah and forsake all whom our forefathers were wont to worship? {1} Then bring upon us the scourge with which you have threatened us if you are truthful?'",footnotes:1:It is worth noting that the people of 'Ad neither disbelieved in God nor refused to worship Him. They did not
7,71,"Hud warned them: 'Surely punishment and wrath from your Lord have befallen upon you. Do you dispute with me about mere names that you and your forefathers have concocted {1} and for which Allah has sent down no sanction? {2} Wait, then, and I too am with you among those who wait.'",footnotes:1:They looked to gods of rain and gods of wind
7,72,"Then We delivered Hud and his companions by Our mercy, and We utterly cut off the last remnant of those who called the lie to Our signs and would not believe. {1}",footnotes:1:The Qur'an informs us that God brought about the total extermination of the 'Ad
7,73,"And to Thamud {1} We sent forth their brother. Salih. He said to them: '0 my people! Serve Allah, you have no other god than Him. Truly there has come to you a clear proof from your Lord. This she-camel from Allah is a Divine portent for you. {2} So leave her alone to pasture on Allah's earth, and touch her with no evil lest a painful chastisement should seize you.",footnotes:1:The Thamud are another ancient Arab people
